						"title": "Driving down IT stack complexity",
						"titleSize": null,
						"subtitle": "A new approach to platform consolidation that improves resilience and reduces risk",
						"subtitleSize": null,
						"copy": "Eighty-eight percent of IT leaders are actively consolidating and optimizing their technology stacks. Platform consolidation — the integration of multiple tools and infrastructure into a single, cohesive platform — is a strategic priority for security and IT leaders, driven by increasing tech stack complexity and economic challenges. Unfortunately, platform consolidation projects often struggle to meet expectations due to gaps between what platforms can do and what it should do. \n\nIn this ebook, learn how to overcome these challenges when it comes to platform consolidation, including:\n- Compatibility issues\n- Misleading vendor promises\n- High switching costs\n- Organizational inertia\n",
